U.K. Currency Trading Rises to $2.19 Trillion a Day

-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 
2011-07-25T13:20:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/u-k-currency-trading-rises-to-2-19-trillion-a-day-correct-.html
(Corrects size of trading in headline, first paragraph.)  U.K. currency turnover rose to a
record $2.19 trillion a day in April, an increase of 23 percent
from October, according to a semi-annual survey of trading
published by the Foreign Exchange Joint Standing Committee.  To contact the reporter on this story:
